claim.claim-text:
1. A digital television receiver, comprising:
a demodulator configured to demodulate an input signal containing first service data multiplexed with second service data;
a first forward error correction (FEC) decoder configured to decode the demodulated signal for first forward error correction (FEC) in order to correct errors in the first and second service data that occurred during reception of the input signal;
a demultiplexer configure to demultiplex the first service data and the second service data from the FEC-decoded signal;
an MPEG header remover configured to remove MPEG headers from the demultiplexed first service data; and
a second forward error correction (FEC) decoder configured to decode the demultiplexed first service data after the headers are removed for second forward error correction (FEC) in order to additionally correct errors in the first service data that occurred during the reception of the input signal.

12. A method of decoding a digital broadcast signal, the method comprising:
demodulating an input signal containing first service data multiplexed with second service data;
decoding the demodulated signal for first forward error correction (FEC) in order to correct errors in the first and second service data that occurred during reception of the input signal;
demultiplexing the first service data and the second service data from the FEC-decoded signal;
removing MPEG headers from the demultiplexed first service data; and
decoding the demultiplexed first service data after the headers are removed for second forward error correction (FEC) in order to additionally correct errors in the first service data that occurred during the reception of the input signal.

22. A broadcast transmitter, comprising:
a first forward error correction (FEC) coder configured to code first service data for first forward error correction (FEC) in order to reduce errors in the first service data that occur during data transmission;
an MPEG header inserter configured to insert MPEG headers in the FEC-coded first service data;
a multiplexer configured to multiplex the FEC-coded first service data containing the MPEG headers with second service data;
a second forward error correction (FEC) coder configured to code the multiplexed first and second service data for second forward error correction (FEC) in order to reduce errors in the first and second service data that occur during data transmission; and
a modulator configured to modulate the FEC-coded first and second service data for data transmission.

33. A method of encoding a digital broadcast signal, the method comprising:
coding first service data for first forward error correction (FEC) in order to reduce errors in the first service data during data transmission;
inserting MPEG headers in the FEC-coded first service data;
multiplexing the FEC-coded first service data containing the MPEG headers with second service data;
coding the multiplexed first and second service data for second forward error correction (FEC) in order to reduce errors in the first and second service data that occur during data transmission; and
modulating the FEC-coded first and second service data for data transmission.

44. A digital television (DTV) receiver, comprising:
a demodulator configured to demodulate a digital television (DTV) signal in which first service data are multiplexed with second service data;
a first decoder configured to decode the demodulated DTV signal for first error correction in order to correct errors in the first and second service data that occurred during reception of the DTV signal;
a data extractor configured to extract the first service data from the DTV signal decoded by the first decoder, and to remove MPEG headers included in the first service data; and
a second decoder configured to decode the header-removed first service data for second error correction in order to additionally correct errors in the first service data that occurred during the reception of the DTV signal.

46. A method of decoding a digital broadcast signal, the method comprising:
demodulating a digital television (DTV) signal in which first service data are multiplexed with second service data;
decoding the demodulated DTV signal for first error correction in order to correct errors in the first and second service data that occurred during reception of the DTV signal;
extracting the first service data from the decoded DTV signal;
removing MPEG headers included in the first service data; and
decoding the header-removed first service data for second error correction in order to additionally correct errors in the first service data that occurred during the reception of the DTV signal.
